  "prompt": "Will there be a sufficient space for rough work in offline mode of JEE?",
  "response": "In the offline mode of the JEE (Joint Entrance Examination), candidates are typically provided with adequate space for rough work. This is usually done on additional sheets of paper specifically allocated for rough calculations and notes. However, the specifics may vary slightly depending on the examination center and the rules set by the organizing body.\n\nIt's important to follow the instructions provided by the exam authorities at the center. Candidates are encouraged to keep their rough work organized, as it can help in the finalizing of answers and aid in calculations. Make sure to check the official guidelines or announcements from the JEE conducting body for the most accurate and updated information.",
